100.2	Centralia,_Pennsylvania	Centralia, Pennsylvania	Centralia is a borough and ghost town in Columbia County, Pennsylvania, United States. Its population has dwindled from over 1,000 residents in 1981 to 12 in 2005, 9 in 2007, and 10 in 2010, as a result of a mine fire burning beneath the borough since 1962. Centralia is one of the least-populated municipalities in Pennsylvania.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2c/Centralia_Skyline.jpg/250px-Centralia_Skyline.jpg
